title: Gustave Caillebotte Paris Street; Rainy Day Umbrella
description:
Umbrella developed from Gustave Caillebotte Paris Street; Rainy Day, 1877, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Step out in style with this tote and umbrella featuring Gustave Caillebotte’s (French, 1848-1894) Paris Street; Rainy Day. Polished and practical, the umbrella features an auto open/close and matching sleeve for easy storage.

  • Dimensions: Closed- 11 x 2 in.  Open – 36 in.
  • Materials: Polyester, aluminum.
  • Auto open, close.
  • Storage sleeve for umbrella included.
